title: Girona vs Arsenal - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Girona will face Arsenal for the very first time; the Spaniards’ most recent home game in the UEFA Champions League also come against an English opponent, losing 1-0 to Liverpool on MD6. Arsenal won their most recent away game against Spanish opposition in the UEFA Champions League, 2-1 at Sevilla in October 2023, last winning back-to-back such matches in the competition in February 2004-February 2006.

title: Barcelona vs Atalanta - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Barcelona and Atalanta will meet for the very first time in a competitive fixture – the Italians will be the 159th different team Barca have faced in European competition, the most different opponents of any side. Atalanta are winless in their last five UEFA Champions League games against Spanish opposition, since beating Valencia in both legs of their 2019-20 last 16 tie.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Brest vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Brest have already lost to Barcelona in this season’s UEFA Champions League, with the last team to lose to both Real Madrid and Barça in their debut campaign in the competition being Leeds United in 2000-01. Real Madrid have lost exactly half of their 14 away games against French opposition in the UEFA Champions League, only posting a higher away loss rate versus Russian opponents in the competition.

title: Manchester City vs Club Brugge - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Manchester City won both of their previous meetings with Club Brugge, winning 5-1 away and 4-1 at home during the 2021-22 UEFA Champions League group stage. Club Brugge have never won away to English opposition in European competition in 14 previous attempts ; only RSC Anderlecht and Dynamo Kyiv have played more such games without ever recording a win in England.

title: Aston Villa vs Celtic - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Aston Villa and Celtic will meet for the very first time; the Villans’ only previous European fixture against a fellow British club came in 2023-24 UEFA Conference League qualifying, winning 8-0 on aggregate against Hibernian. Celtic have drawn each of their last three games against English opposition in the UEFA Champions League, drawing 1-1 at the Etihad Stadium with Manchester City in their most recent such game in December 2016.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Internazionale vs Monaco - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Internazionale have won their two previous home games in European competition against Monaco, winning 1-0 in the 1963-64 European Cup round of 16 and 3-1 in the 1996-97 UEFA Cup semi-finals. Monaco lost each of their first three games against Internazionale in European competition but did win their most recent meeting with them in April 1997 in the UEFA Cup.

title: Stuttgart vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: Stuttgart have lost only one of their four previous meetings at home with a French opponent in European competition, though that did come in their most recent such match, losing 2-0 to Lyon in the 2007-08 UEFA Champions League group stage. Paris SG have lost eight of their 13 away games in the UEFA Champions League against German opposition, holding their joint-worst win rate on the road in the competition against German teams.

title: Salzburg vs Atletico Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 MD8
description: RB Salzburg and Atletico de Madrid have met twice previously in all competitions with both coming the 2020-21 UEFA Champions League group stage; the Spaniards won 3-2 away on MD2 and 2-0 at home on MD6. Atletico de Madrid have never lost against an Austrian opponent in European competition, winning nine of their 10 such matches to date. They’ve won all four of their games against Austrian sides under Diego Simeone by an aggregate score of 12-2.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Brest vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This will be the first time ever that both Brest and Paris SG have faced a fellow French side in European competition. The only previous UEFA Champions League tie between two French clubs was the 2009-10 quarter-final between Bordeaux and Lyon, from which Lyon progressed 3-2 on aggregate. Paris SG are unbeaten in their last 30 matches against Brest across all competitions, with their last defeat against them coming in January 1985. Indeed, they’ve already beaten Brest on two occasions in 2024-25.

title: Sporting CP vs Borussia Dortmund - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This will be the fifth meeting in European competition between Sporting CP and Borussia Dortmund, with each of the previous four all coming in the UEFA Champions League group stage; BVB won the first three but the Lions won the most recent in November 2021, 3-1 at Estádio Jose Alvalade. Borussia Dortmund have a better win rate against teams from Portugal than against sides from any other nation they have faced more than 10 times in European competition; meanwhile Sporting CP have suffered more defeats to German opposition than any other nation.

title: Manchester City vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: Manchester City versus Real Madrid will be just the fourth fixture in European Cup/UEFA Champions League history to played in four consecutive seasons, after Deportivo de La Coruña v Juventus, Chelsea v Liverpool, and Atletico de Madrid v Real Madrid. This will be the 13th time Manchester City have faced Real Madrid in the UEFA Champions League. Of opponents Real Madrid have played against 5+ times in their European Cup/Champions League history, their win percentage of 25% against the Citizens is their lowest against any opponent.

title: Juventus vs PSV - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This is just the second meeting between Juventus and PSV Eindhoven in major European competition, with the only previous meeting also coming this season, a 3-1 victory for Juventus at home in September 2024 in league phase. Juventus have lost just three of their 15 matches against Dutch oppositions in the UEFA Champions League/European Cup, winning seven of their last 11.

title: Manchester City vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: Manchester City versus Real Madrid will be just the fourth fixture in European Cup/UEFA Champions League history to played in four consecutive seasons, after Deportivo de La Coruña v Juventus, Chelsea v Liverpool, and Atletico de Madrid v Real Madrid. This will be the 13th time Manchester City have faced Real Madrid in the UEFA Champions League. Of opponents Real Madrid have played against 5+ times in their European Cup/Champions League history, their win percentage of 25% against the Citizens is their lowest against any opponent.

title: Club Brugge vs Atalanta - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This will be the first European meeting between Club Brugge and Atalanta. The Belgian side are winless in their last 15 games against Italian sides in major European competition, since winning 1-0 away to Milan in October 2003 in the UEFA Champions League. Club Brugge’s last home win against an Italian side came back in April 1978, in a 2-0 victory over Juventus in the UEFA Cup. Since then, they haven’t won any of the nine times they’ve hosted Italian opposition in Europe, although have avoided defeat in the last three, including one this season.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Monaco vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This will be the fourth meeting between these two sides in European competition, with Benfica unbeaten against their French counterparts in all three meetings, winning one and drawing one in the UEFA Champions League group stage in 2014-15 and winning last time out, in Monaco in the league phase this season. Monaco have failed to score in two of their three meetings with Benfica in Europe, although they did manage to bag two goals last time out, in a 3-2 home defeat in the UEFA Champions League league phase this season.

title: Celtic vs Bayern Munchen - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: Celtic have faced Bayern Munich on four previous occasions in European competition, going winless across all four in the group stages of the UEFA Champions League. Bayern Munich are unbeaten in their last 13 matches against Scottish sides in major European competition, with their last such defeat coming against Hearts in the UEFA Cup in February 1989.

title: Feyenoord vs Milan - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 1st Leg
description: This will be just the third meeting between Feyenoord and Milan in European competition, with the pair winning one match each during their two-legged European Cup Round of Last 16 clash during the 1969-70 season – the Dutch team progressed to the next round. Milan have failed to win any of their last four games in major European competition against sides from the Netherlands, since a 3-1 win over SC Heerenveen in the UEFA Cup in October 2008.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Milan vs Feyenoord - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Milan have lost two of their three meetings with Feyenoord in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League, although both of those defeats have come away. Their only home game against them was a 1-0 victory in November 1969. Feyenoord have lost five of their six away games against Italian sides in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League, only managing to avoid defeat in February 2000 v Lazio. Indeed, the only one of those six games to take place in the knockout stages was a 0-1 defeat to Milan in the 1969-70 campaign.

title: Benfica vs Monaco - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Benfica have won both of their matches against Monaco this season. They’ve never previously won more games against the same opponent in a European campaign, while the last side to beat an opponent three times in the same season in the UEFA Champions League was Barcelona versus Paris SG in 2014-15. Should Monaco fail to win this game, Benfica will become the team they have faced most often in major European competition without managing a victory.

title: Atalanta vs Club Brugge - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Atalanta progressed from their first two major European ties after losing the first leg in the 1987-88 Cup Winners’ Cup against Merthyr Tydfil and OFI but they have been eliminated in their last three ties when losing the first leg since then. Club Brugge won the first leg against Atalanta 2-1 but they have been eliminated on 16 occasions in major European competitions when they’ve won the first leg of a knockout tie, more than any other side in history.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: Bayern Munchen vs Celtic - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Bayern Munich have won their last five home European matches against Scottish opponents and have never lost at home against a Scottish team. Celtic have been eliminated in their last nine major European knockout ties when they’ve lost the first leg, since going through against 1. FC Koln in the first round of the 1992-93 UEFA Cup. They’ve never progressed when losing the first leg at home, however.

title: Borussia Dortmund vs Sporting CP - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Borussia Dortmund’s 3-0 win in the first leg was the 12th time they’ve won the first leg of a major European knockout stage tie away from home – they’ve progressed each of the previous 11. Borussia Dortmund have won four of their five meetings with Sporting CP in all competitions, with both of their previous home games against them finishing 1-0.

title: PSV vs Juventus - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: 21% of Manuel Locatelli’s passes in the UEFA Champions League this season have broken at least one opposition line; the highest percentage by any player in 2024-25. Indeed, the Juventus man is one of only three midfielders with 100+ line-breaking passes in the competition overall this term, along with Joshua Kimmich and Angelo Stiller. In the form of Francisco Conceiçao and Kenan Yildiz, this is the first UEFA Champions League campaign since 2014-15 in which two Juventus players have both completed 20+ dribbles – Carlos Tevez and Álvaro Morata both did so that season, in a team that finished as runners-up.

title: England vs Spain - UEFA Womens EURO 2025 - Championship Switzerland - Finals
description: The UEFA Womens EURO 2025 – Championship is the 14th edition of the UEFA Women’s Championship, Switzerland is hosting the tournament from 2 till 27 July 2025 with 16 national teams competing to win the title.

title: PSG vs Brest - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Paris SG’s 3-0 victory in the first leg against Brest was the 19th time they’ve won the first leg of a European knockout tie away from home – they’ve progressed from 17 of the previous 18, failing only against Manchester United in the 2018-19 UEFA Champions League. Brest trail by three goals in this tie against Paris SG, following their first leg defeat. No side has ever progressed from a two-legged UEFA Champions League knockout stage tie, having lost the first leg at home by three or more goals.

title: Real Madrid vs Manchester City - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Knoch Out Play-offs - 2nd Leg
description: Real Madrid’s 3-2 win in the first leg against Man City was the 40th time they’ve won the first leg of a European knockout stage tie away from home – they’ve progressed from 37 of the previous 39, failing only against Odense Boldklub and Ajax. Man City’s 3-2 defeat in the first leg was the fifth time they’ve lost the first leg of a UEFA Champions League knockout stage tie, going on to be eliminated on each of the previous four occasions.

title: FCSB vs Lyon - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 1st Leg
description: This will be the first season whereby the UEFA Europa League will be played under a new format, which replaces the 32-team group stage with a 36-team league phase. The new format also does not allow teams to transfer from the Champions League knockout stage to the Europa League knockout stage. The final will be played on 21 May 2025 at San Mames stadium in Bilbao, Spain.All matches are live and exclusive only on beIN.
